<%# Phase 1D gap fix (2026-05-24). Meilisearch section of the Stack pane,
    extracted so the Meilisearch reindex job can broadcast a Turbo Stream
    replace targeted at the wrapping `<div id="meilisearch_section">`
    without re-rendering the entire stack pane.

    Mirrors the Voyage section partial pattern exactly:

      * idle    — nothing extra rendered; the `[reindex]` action on the
                  title row (parent chrome) is live. The idle state here
                  is intentionally empty so the broadcast only replaces
                  the running-state strip.
      * running — renders the `dot-loader` `=/-` compound loading
                  indicator (`.dot-loader` in
                  `tailwind/application.css`) + a small
                  "reindexing... started ~Xs ago" line driven by the
                  existing `compact_time_ago` helper.

    The wrapping id matches the broadcast target inside
    `MeilisearchReindexJob#broadcast_meilisearch_section`. The view reads
    the flag fresh every render so the post-redirect page load already
    shows the running state without waiting for the broadcast.

    The `[reindex]` action and stats table both live in the parent
    `Pito::Stack::MeilisearchSubPanelComponent` template and are NOT
    clobbered by this replace (same split as Voyage). %>
<% reindex_running = AppSetting.reindex_running? %>
<div id="meilisearch_section">
  <% if reindex_running %>
    <%# Running state. Reuses the `.dot-loader` `=/- ` indicator
        from the Sync progress page (definition in
        `app/assets/tailwind/application.css`). The randomized
        `--loader-delay` matches the convention in
        `syncs/progress.html.erb` and `_voyage_section.html.erb`. %>
    <div class="dot-list" style="margin-top: 4px;">
      <span class="dot-loader" style="--loader-delay: -0.25s"></span>
      <span class="text-muted" style="margin-left: 6px;">
        <%= t("settings.meilisearch.reindexing_html", time_ago: compact_time_ago(AppSetting.reindex_started_at)) %>
      </span>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
